⸻

4. Competitive Differentiators (Apparel)

vs. Fast Fashion
	•	Higher quality materials
	•	Ethical production
	•	Longer-lasting
	•	Better fit and comfort

vs. Premium Competitors
	•	Better price-to-quality ratio
	•	More innovative fabrics
	•	Better fit for diverse body types
	•	Better customer service, guarantees, or exchanges

vs. Outdoor / Activewear Brands
	•	More stylish
	•	Less branding
	•	More comfortable
	•	More versatile (gym → work → weekend)

⸻

5. Use Cases by Customer Segment

Segment 1: The Everyday Comfort Wearer
	•	Needs: Clothes that feel good all day
	•	Pain Points: Uncomfortable seams, shrinking fabrics
	•	How the Product Helps:

Segment 2: The Active Lifestyle Customer
	•	Needs: Breathable, flexible, sweat-resistant
	•	Pain Points: Cheap activewear losing shape
	•	How the Product Helps:

Segment 3: The Style-Conscious Shopper
	•	Needs: Trendy but timeless designs
	•	Pain Points: Fast fashion quality
	•	How the Product Helps:

Segment 4: The Workwear / Functional Apparel Customer
	•	Needs: Durability, mobility, all-weather performance
	•	Pain Points: Work clothes that don’t last
	•	How the Product Helps:

